A vintage 1940s-style illustration of an archaeologist carefully excavating layers of an ancient technological dig site, where each stratum reveals different eras of computer hardware and tangled cables instead of fossils and pottery shards. The archaeologist uses delicate brushes and tools to uncover a glowing amber-toned database structure buried deep in sedimentary layers of floppy disks, circuit boards, and old server racks. Warm sepia tones dominate with pops of dusty gold light emanating from the discovered digital artifacts. The scene conveys careful investigation and the excitement of understanding something complex and historical, rendered in the style of mid-century scientific expedition posters with crosshatching and muted earth colors.
